This statement by the President commemorates the one-year anniversary of the Boston Marathon bombing. The President remembers the four innocent people who lost their lives and sends thoughts and prayers to those still recovering. He highlights the acts of compassion, kindness, and strength that were witnessed on that day. The President praises the courage and leadership of the Boston community and expresses gratitude to the firefighters, police officers, medical professionals, runners, and spectators who displayed the spirit of Boston. He also acknowledges the resilience of the survivors and the inspiration they continue to provide. The statement concludes by mentioning the upcoming Boston Marathon and how it will demonstrate the city's resilience and unity.